<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-20T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-20T12:36:00-05:00" n="1171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1171">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5001.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-20T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The importance of either retaining Pasqual Orozco, sr., on American soil
                            or returning him to Mexico at a point held by revolutionists is a matter
                            I wish to bring urgently before the Department. Ernesto Madero says it
                            had been arranged for Governor Gonzalez, of Chihuahua, * * *<note n="1" xml:id="d1171fn1">Omission in transmission.</note> and that he will
                            be immediately shot. Gonzalez is implacably anti-American, a menace to
                            American interests, who should be treated with small courtesy. The
                            surrender of Orozco to the Federal Government’s man under any guise or
                            pretext would work incalculable harm to defenseless Americans and
                            American interests in districts held by the revolutionary forces.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>